# CTK Case08: Intent Type Signature Validation

This test case validates that intent input and output type signatures are correctly validated.

## CDL Specification

```cdl
type UserCredentials
  username: string where length(username) >= 3
  password: string where length(password) >= 8
end

type UserProfile
  id: string
  username: string
  email: Email
  createdAt: datetime
end

type LoginRequest
  credentials: UserCredentials
  rememberMe: bool
end

type LoginResponse
  success: bool
  user: UserProfile
  token: string
  expiresAt: datetime
end

type ErrorResponse
  errorCode: string
  message: string
  timestamp: datetime
end

intent AUTHENTICATE_USER
  goal: "Authenticate user with credentials"
  inputs: "[request: LoginRequest]"
  outputs: "[response: LoginResponse, error: ErrorResponse]"
  evidence: "[authentication_protocol_v3]"
  tags: "[auth, security, login]"
end

intent LOGOUT_USER
  goal: "Log out authenticated user"
  inputs: "[token: string, userId: string]"
  outputs: "[success: bool]"
  evidence: "[session_management_spec]"
  tags: "[auth, logout]"
end

mapping AUTHENTICATE_USER -> "api POST /api/auth/login"
  request: "LoginRequest"
  response: "LoginResponse"
end

mapping LOGOUT_USER -> "api POST /api/auth/logout"
  request: "LogoutRequest"
  response: "LogoutResponse"
end
```

## Expected Validation
- ✅ Intent inputs reference valid types
- ✅ Intent outputs reference valid types
- ✅ Type signatures are properly structured
- ✅ Complex input/output combinations work
